---
title: Spicy & Sweet Soy-Glazed Beef Tenderloin with Roasted Carrots & Broccoli
description: When it comes to elevating a simple weeknight meal—like our dear friend, the humble pork chop—it’s all about the pan sauce! In this case, you’ll get a great sear on the pork, then coat it in a tangy-sweet soy sauce thickened with butter to glossy perfection. On the side is roasted broccoli and carrots sprinkled with fiery Korean chili flakes. Shower your plate with scallion greens before serving for a fresh, zippy crunch.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65f9d3f0c9eee2bcbf31fdc5-9524464c.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/668ee74a0da5ee2a714177b8-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spicy-and-sweet-soy-glazed-beef-tenderloin-668ee74a0da5ee2a714177b8
course: main course
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Asian
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 550 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 37 g
  sugar: 23 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 910 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli{1%unit} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens.

Toss broccoli on one side of a #baking sheet with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss carrots on empty side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, a pinch of @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

> For 4 servings, spread broccoli out across entire baking sheet. Add carrots to a separate #baking sheet{}; roast broccoli on top rack and carrots on middle rack.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until tender and crisp, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels and season all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining chili flakes, salt, and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

> Swap in chicken or pork for beef. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side, or cook pork to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon} and @water{1/4%cup}; simmer until bubbling and slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 1/3 cup water.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted.

> Use pan used for chicken or beef here.

Slice beef crosswise.

Add beef to pan with sauce and toss to coat.

> Slice chicken or pork against the grain and toss with sauce as instructed.

Divide carrots, broccoli, and glazed beef between plates. Drizzle any remaining sauce from pan over beef. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.